<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,917,1161]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,990,1016]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Topsent" authorityYear="1901" box="[447,604,990,1016]" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[447,604,990,1016]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Asbestopluma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recently summarised, including remeasuring the spicule dimensions of some old 
<typeStatus box="[359,421,1027,1053]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">types</typeStatus>
, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes" box="[469,683,1026,1053]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Lopes" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="407 - 443" refId="ref75430" refString="Lopes, D. A., Bravo, A. &amp; Hajdu, E. (2011) New carnivorous sponges (Cladorhizidae: Poecilosclerida: Demospongiae) from off Diego Ramirez Archipelago (south Chile), with comments on taxonomy and biogeography of the family. Invertebrate Systematics, 25, 407 - 443. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 11015" type="journal article" year="2011">
Lopes 
<emphasis box="[545,602,1026,1052]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Goodwin" box="[740,994,1026,1052]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Goodwin" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="37 - 64" refId="ref73334" refString="Goodwin, C. E., Berman, J., Downey, R. V. &amp; Hendry, K. R. (2017) Carnivorous sponges (Porifera: Demospongiae: Poecilosclerida: Cladorhizidae) from the Drake Passage (Southern Ocean) with a description of eight new species and a review of the family Cladorhizidae in the Southern Ocean. Invertebrate Systematics, 31 (1), 37 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 16020" type="journal article" year="2017">
Goodwin 
<emphasis box="[852,909,1026,1052]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
, with these data updated to include additional information, and more recently described species, in 
<tableCitation box="[852,940,1062,1088]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="29.[151,239,534,560]" captionTargetBox="[162,2030,611,1564]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="TABLE 4. Comparative morphological and distributional data for all known species of Asbestopluma." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF04662891533B05FF7EFDADFB24FDAD" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" tableUuid="DF04662891533B05FF7EFDADFB24FDAD">Table 4</tableCitation>
. There has been two species recorded from the Australian EEZ, viz. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kelly &amp; Vacelet, 2011" authorityName="Kelly &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2011" box="[441,1201,1098,1124]" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="desmophora" subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[441,932,1098,1124]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Asbestopluma (Asbestopluma) desmophora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kelly &amp; Vacelet" box="[942,1201,1098,1124]" firstAuthor="Kelly" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="55 - 68" refId="ref74303" refString="Kelly, M. &amp; Vacelet, J. (2011) Three new remarkable carnivorous sponges (Porifera, Cladorhizidae) from deep New Zealand and Australian (Macquarie Island) waters. Zootaxa, 2976 (1), 55 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2976.1.4" type="journal article" year="2011">Kelly &amp; Vacelet, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Seamounts on Macquarie Ridge, SE Pacific, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Koltun, 1964" authorityName="Koltun" authorityYear="1964" box="[538,828,1134,1161]" class="Demospongiae" family="Cladorhizidae" genus="Asbestopluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="obae" subGenus="Asbestopluma">
<emphasis box="[538,672,1134,1161]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">A. (A.) obae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Koltun" box="[680,828,1134,1160]" firstAuthor="Koltun" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="6 - 133" refId="ref74693" refString="Koltun, V. M. (1964) Sponges of the Antarctic. 1 Tetraxonida and Cornacuspongida. In: Pavlovskii, E. P., Andriyashev, A. P. &amp; Ushakov, P. V. (Eds.), Biological Reports of the Soviet Antarctic Expedition (1955 - 1958), 1964, pp. 6 - 133 + 443 - 448." type="journal article" year="1964">Koltun, 1964</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Wilkes Land, 
<collectingCountry box="[1051,1171,1134,1160]" name="Antarctica" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
